## IV. The Three Debate (Compositional)

```limn
was: you los | you gon | you don
```

**Was:** You [are] lost. You [are] gone. You [are] done.

> *The past claims: You are already lost, already gone, already finished. Everything meaningful has ended.*

```limn
now: you her | you ali | you bre
```

**Now:** You [are] here. You [are] alive. You [are] breathing.

> *The present counters: You are here. You are alive right now. You are breathing this moment.*

```limn
wil: you bec | you gro | you cha
```

**Will:** You [are] becoming. You [are] growing. You [are] changing.

> *The future argues: You are in the process of becoming. You are still growing. You are changing into something new.*

```limn
sel: you = was±now±wil
```

**Self:** You [all] = past±present±future.

> *The self realizes: All three are true simultaneously. I am what was, what is, and what will be, all at once.*

