## V. On Identity

```limn
sel ask was: who you?
was: who you wer | sel@pas | mem you
```

**Self asks Was:** Who [are] you?
**Was:** Who you were. Self-at-past. Memory [of] you.

> *The past is who you were. The self projected onto the past. Memory of your former being.*

```limn
sel ask now: who you?
now: who you = now | sel@pre | exp you
```

**Self asks Now:** Who [are] you?
**Now:** Who you are now. Self-at-present. Experience [of] you.

> *The present is who you are. The self in the present moment. Direct experience of being.*

```limn
sel ask wil: who you?
wil: who you bec | sel@fut | pos you
```

**Self asks Will:** Who [are] you?
**Will:** Who you [will] become. Self-at-future. Possibility [of] you.

> *The future is who you will become. The self projected forward. Potential versions of you.*

```limn
sel: you = (sel@was) * (sel@now) * (sel@wil)
```

**Self:** You [all together] = (self-at-past) TIMES (self-at-present) TIMES (self-at-future).

> *Identity is the interference pattern of all three temporal projections of self, interacting simultaneously.*

