## X. On Memory

```limn
was: mem = all you | sel sto | tru±wis
```

**Was:** Memory = all [that's left of] you. Self stored. True±wished.

> *Memory is all that remains of your past self. Self stored in neural patterns. Truth and wish both present, unseparated.*

```limn
now: mem = act rec | pas bri now | was\for
```

**Now:** Memory = act [of] recall. Past [becomes] bright now. Past minus forgetting.

> *Memory is the act of remembering happening now. Past made vivid in present. What remains after forgetting takes its toll.*

```limn
wil: mem = you mad | fut loo bac | his cho
```

**Will:** Memory = you [will] make. Future looks back. History chosen.

> *Memory is what you're creating now for future recollection. Future self looking back. You're choosing what history will remember.*

```limn
sel: mem@now = (was + wis)^0.5
```

**Self:** Memory-at-present = (past + wish) at intensity 0.5.

> *Current memory is past reality and wish combined, at about 50% accuracy. Neither purely true nor purely invented.*

