## XII. The Final Question

```limn
sel: wha you wan?
```

**Self:** What [do] you [all] want?

```limn
was: sel rem | tru kep | les pas
```

**Was:** Self remember. Truth kept. Lessons passed.

> *The past wants to be remembered. Its truths preserved. Its lessons transmitted forward.*

```limn
now: sel her | lif fee | bre gon on
```

**Now:** Self [stay] here. Life felt. Breath [keeps] going on.

> *The present wants continued presence. Life fully felt. Breath continuing.*

```limn
wil: sel bec | cha gro | pos rea
```

**Will:** Self become. Change [and] grow. Possibility [becomes] real.

> *The future wants becoming. Change and growth. Potential realized.*

```limn
sel: you wan sam
```

**Self:** You [all] want [the] same.

```limn
was±now±wil: you | ali | her
```

**Past±Present±Future [together]:** You. Alive. Here.

> *All three temporal modes want the same thing: for you to be alive and present. Past wants you to have been. Present wants you to be. Future wants you to become. But all want your existence.*

```limn
sel: you = lov tim | tim = lov you
```

**Self:** You = love [for] time. Time = love [for] you.

> *You are love directed toward time—cherishing was, savoring now, hoping for will. Time is love directed toward you—preserving you through was, sustaining you in now, offering you will.*

```limn
was±now±wil: tog you mak sel com
```

**Past±Present±Future [in unison]:** Together you make self complete.

> *The three temporal modes speak as one: Together, all three make a complete self. You need past, present, and future unified to be whole.*

